5, 0], [25, 23], [25, 46], [25, 69], [25, 92], [25, 115], [25, 138], [25, 161], [25, 184], [25, 207], [25, 230], [25, 253], [25, 276], [25, 299], [25, 322], [25, 345], [25, 368], [25, 391], [25, 414], [26, 0], [26, 23], [26, 46], [26, 69], [26, 92], [26, 115], [26, 138], [26, 161], [26, 184], [26, 207], [26, 230], [26, 253], [26, 276], [26, 299], [26, 322], [26, 345], [26, 368], [26, 391], [26, 414], [26, 437], [26, 460], [27, 0], [27, 23], [27, 46], [27, 69], [27, 92], [27, 115], [27, 138], [27, 161], [27, 184], [28, 0], [28, 23], [28, 46], [28, 69], [28, 92], [28, 115], [28, 138], [28, 161], [28, 184], [28, 207], [28, 230], [28, 253], [28, 276], [28, 299], [28, 322], [29, 0], [29, 23], [29, 46], [29, 69], [29, 92], [29, 115], [29, 138], [29, 161], [29, 184]]}, "lines": {"text": ["Relational Mindfulness Agreements", "We offer the following agreements* to ensure that all members of our community are able to bring their whole", "selves as freely and safely as possible to all of our discussions. We ask that you reflect on these carefully and", "bring mindful awareness of these intentions to all interactions.", "\u200bBe willing to \u201ctry on\u201d new ideas or ways of doing things that might not be what you prefer or are", "TRY IT ON:\u200b", "familiar with.", "Approach interactions seeking to better SEEK UNDERSTANDING INSTEAD OF AGREEMENT:\u200b", "understand others, rather than convincing them you\u2019re right. \u201cI don\u2019t understand\u201d instead of \u201cI disagree\u201d helps", "you learn how the experience of others differs from yours.", "Attend to and speak about your own experiences and responses. Do not speak PRACTICE SELF FOCUS:\u200b", "for a whole group or express assumptions about the experience of others.", "\u200bTry to understand and UNDERSTAND THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN INTENT AND IMPACT:\u200b", "acknowledge impact. Denying the impact of something said by focusing on \u201cgood intentions\u201d is often more", "destructive than the initial interaction.", "When speaking, substitute \u201cand\u201d for \u201cbut.\u201d This practice acknowledges and PRACTICE \u201cBOTH / AND\u201d:\u200b", "honors multiple realities.", "Practice giving skillful, non-judgmental REFRAIN FROM BLAMING OR SHAMING SELF & OTHERS:\u200b", "feedback. We are all still growing.", "Encourage full participation by all present. Take note of who is speaking and MOVE UP / MOVE BACK:\u200b", "who is not. If you tend to speak often, consider \u201cmoving back\u201d and vice versa.", "Try to avoid planning what you\u2019ll say as you listen to others. Listen PRACTICE MINDFUL LISTENING:\u200b", "with your whole self, and try to maintain awareness of your body as you listen. Be willing to be surprised, to", "learn something new.", "home learnings but don\u2019t identify anyone other than yourself, now or later. If you CONFIDENTIALITY: \u200bTake", "want to follow up with anyone regarding something they said in this session, ask first and respect their wishes.", "You can say \u201cI pass\u201d if you don\u2019t wish to speak. If someone else chooses to pass, respect RIGHT TO PASS:\u200b", "their wish rather than trying to change their mind.", "* Adapted from similar agreements used by Visions Inc. and the East Bay Meditation Center.", "\u00a9 Mindful Schools is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization. www.mindfulschools.org"], "bbox": [[0.247549, 0.123906, 0.514832, 0.025246], [0.058824, 0.161154, 0.881356, 0.018936], [0.058824, 0.180093, 0.867777, 0.018936], [0.058824, 0.199033, 0.4963390000000001, 0.018936], [0.172628, 0.239753, 0.769962, 0.018936], [0.058824, 0.237196, 0.109171, 0.022385], [0.058824, 0.259639, 0.103421, 0.018936], [0.582194, 0.297802, -0.004634000000000027, 0.022385], [0.058824, 0.320245, 0.873093, 0.018936], [0.058824, 0.339184, 0.46192500000000003, 0.018936], [0.306984, 0.377348, -0.004632999999999998, 0.022385], [0.058824, 0.39979, 0.588731, 0.018936], [0.732094, 0.437954, -0.004866000000000037, 0.022385], [0.058824, 0.460397, 